      <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>I will rework the chapters of the 3 bible versions into a table. That should shorten the page without losing any information. In fact it adds information. <a href="/wiki/User:Robert_Marquardt" title="User:Robert Marquardt">Robert Marquardt</a> 07:10, 1 January 2007 (EST)
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Who_is_Christian.3F">Who is Christian?</span></h2>
<p>Re: removal of Church of Latter Day Saints and Christian Science.  <a href="/wiki/User:Freeelf" title="User:Freeelf">User:Freeelf</a> in good faith removed these two groups from <a href="/wiki/Christianity_(Bookshelf)" title="Christianity (Bookshelf)">Christianity (Bookshelf)</a>.  I have re-added them and this is my justification.  Many Christians feel that LDS (and I guess Christian Scientists?) are not Christian.  By adding them I do not intend to claim that they are Christian nor give them legitimacy as such.  That is a religious decision.  I have re-added them because they are studied in academia as Christian denominations.  The best indicator of this might be the Library of Congress Classification system which keeps books about Mormonism and Christian Science under BX, "Christian Denominations".  These groups also identify themselves as Christians and therefore--whether you believe this or not--they are studied as Christians.
</p><p>This bookshelf is for books related to Christianity--not Christian books.  A good parallel might be books critical of Christianity.  We would not remove a book titled <i>Why Christians Are Evil</i> because it was not Christian since its subject matter is of relevance to this bookshelf.  Likewise, whether or not Mormons and Christian Scientists are "true Christians" should not be a matter for debate on Project Gutenberg.  The question is, do these books relate to the Christianity bookshelf?  I think by using the Library of Congress Classification and subject keys from these books that they are definitely related and relevant to this bookshelf.
</p><p>Thanks, <a href="/wiki/User:Grenavitar" title="User:Grenavitar">Grenavitar</a> 14:32, 9 December 2007 (EST)
</p>
